Create a Fundraising Performance Analytics App

A guided flow walks you through creating an app from the Fundraising Performance Analytics template.

Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition. Requires a CRM Analytics license.

To create and manage the Fundraising Performance Analytics app: Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps
To use the Fundraising Performance Analytics app: Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps

Before creating an app, make sure:

Your org has data stored in the Opportunity object.
The Analytics Integration User has the appropriate Salesforce field-level security to view fields.

For best results from the app, ensure:

Your org has at least 3 years of data in standard objects used in the Nonprofit Success Pack, including Contact, Account, Opportunity (Donation), and User objects.
The Opportunity (Donation) object includes Closed Won stage type.
Your org uses Campaign object to indicate donation's type of program or segment.

Exclude large one-time gifts, which can distort results.

From the Analytics tab or Analytics Studio, click Create, select App, then choose Fundraising Performance Analytics template to open guided flow. Name and save your app.
title: Create Fundraising Performance Analytics App in Salesforce
